http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Sify-initiative/article13978178.ece

The city will be home to another major IT facility. Sify Technologies, an Integrated ICT solutions and Services Provider announced on Saturday said that they will set up its Global Delivery Centre which will be its largest in the country. The 2,00,000 sft. delivery centre would focus on supporting the partnership through the development of solutions for the Third Platform or SMAC (Social, Mobile, Analytics and Cloud Platform).Sify Technologies and Fujitsu Limited also announced that they will collaborate to strengthen their global approaches to developing new customers and markets.Chairman of Sify Technologies, Raju Vegesna, said the centre would support the company’s applications and system—integration resources globally.Speaking on this occasion, Telangana IT Minister K.T. Rama Rao reiterated that that they are determined to position Telangana as the preferred destination for IT companies in India.